A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Troy Taylor; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Troy Taylor's interest in art began while working as a fine art poster repair clerk
3 at Bruce McGaw Graphics during his sophomore year of college, a passion that steadily grew
4 during his distinguished career in engineering and corporate leadership; and
5 WHEREAS, in 2009, inspired by his global travels, he founded ZuCot Gallery in Atlanta's
6 Castleberry Hill neighborhood, transforming a dirt-floor commercial space into a
7 contemporary fine arts gallery; and
8 WHEREAS, he named the gallery in tribute to his paternal grandmother, Frances Ann
9 Taylor, who was among the first women permitted to own a stall in the local produce market
10 within the British colony of Saint Christopher, now St. Kitts, where she developed the
11 reputation of being "as tough as a ZOO CAT"; and
12 WHEREAS, in 2011, Troy Taylor attended an art show held by Onaje and Omari Henderson,
13 owners of Premier Art, who had built a platform to showcase and market African American
14 artists after recognizing a gap in art education and accessibility; and
