15 WHEREAS, Troy Taylor partnered with the Henderson brothers in 2012 to re-brand ZuCot
16 Gallery with a primary focus on the works of living African American artists, forming "The
17 Art Brothers" and adopting the philosophy that art is a reflection of one's personal character
18 and values; and
19 WHEREAS, ZuCot Gallery has since grown into the largest African American fine arts
20 gallery in the southeastern United States, representing artists from across the country and
21 attracting a diverse clientele; and
22 WHEREAS, the gallery has hosted countless events for congressmen, senators, supreme
23 court justices, mayors, professional organizations, Fortune 500 companies, students, and the
24 public, earning its reputation as a hub for networking, education, and cultural engagement;
25 and
26 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable individual be
27 appropriately honored.
28 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
29 recognize and commend Troy Taylor, founder of ZuCot Gallery, for his many outstanding
30 contributions on behalf of the arts as well as extend best wishes for continued success.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
32 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Troy Taylor.
